Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Submit Expense Report, Attach Receipt
   Explanation: The use case "Attach Receipt" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Submit Expense Report"). "Attach Receipt" is not associated with any actor directly, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not involved in any generalization. It represents a sub-step of submitting an expense report rather than a complete, standalone service providing an observable result to a user. This is a textbook example of functional decomposition — breaking down the "Submit Expense Report" behavior into an artificially separated inclusion fragment that has no independent value.
